"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "6025: sin, and God's character",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6025",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>In his righteousness and holiness, God detests sin and its effects upon humanity. In his mercy and grace, he makes available a means of atonement, by the death and resurrection of Jesus Christ.</p>\n<h2>God's character and sin</h2>\n<h3>God himself is perfect</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab1:13\">HAB 1:13</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:5\">1JN 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut32:4\">DEU 32:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Josh24:19\">JOS 24:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps97:2\">PSA 97:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa6:3\">ISA 6:3</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ is sinless</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:22\">1PE 2:22</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa53:9\">ISA 53:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb1:9\">HEB 1:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb7:26-Heb7:27\">HEB 7:26–7:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:5\">1JN 3:5</a></p>\n<h3>God's people are to be holy</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:15-1Pet1:16\">1PE 1:15–1:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:44\">LEV 11:44</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev11:45\">LEV 11:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:2\">LEV 19:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev20:7\">LEV 20:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:48\">MAT 5:48</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:7\">1TH 4:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John3:3\">1JN 3:3</a></p>\n<h2>God's attitude to sin</h2>\n<h3>God knows all sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:17\">JER 16:17</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job10:14\">JOB 10:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:1-Ps139:4\">PSA 139:1–139:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer2:22\">JER 2:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos7:2\">HOS 7:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos5:12\">AMO 5:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:13\">HEB 4:13</a></p>\n<h3>God grieves over sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:6\">GEN 6:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:10\">ISA 63:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a></p>\n<h3>God hates sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps11:5\">PSA 11:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut25:16\">DEU 25:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam11:27\">2SA 11:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps5:5\">PSA 5:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov6:16-Prov6:19\">PRO 6:16–6:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech8:17\">ZEC 8:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke16:15\">LUK 16:15</a></p>\n<h3>Sin provokes God's anger</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:18\">ROM 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr36:16\">2CH 36:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek20:8\">EZK 20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Amos1:3\">AMO 1:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:36\">JHN 3:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph5:5-Eph5:6\">EPH 5:5–5:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5-Col3:6\">COL 3:5–3:6</a></p>\n<h3>God is also merciful and gracious</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:6-Exod34:7\">EXO 34:6–34:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:17\">NEH 9:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:31\">NEH 9:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps78:38\">PSA 78:38</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps103:8-Ps103:14\">PSA 103:8–103:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lam3:22-Lam3:23\">LAM 3:22–3:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mic7:18-Mic7:19\">MIC 7:18–7:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom11:32\">ROM 11:32</a></p>\n<h3>God's patience with sinners</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:9\">2PE 3:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:4\">ROM 2:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom9:22\">ROM 9:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:16\">1TI 1:16</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ is the supreme revelation of God's love for sinners</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ's ministry of forgiveness</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim1:15\">1TI 1:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:2\">MAT 9:2</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:5\">MRK 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:20-Luke5:21\">LUK 5:20–5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke7:36-Luke7:50\">LUK 7:36–7:50</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke15:1-Luke15:10\">LUK 15:1–15:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke19:5-Luke19:10\">LUK 19:5–19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:1-John8:11\">JHN 8:1–8:11</a></p>\n<h3>God's love shown in Jesus Christ's death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:8\">ROM 5:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John3:16-John3:17\">JHN 3:16–3:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph2:4\">EPH 2:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John4:9-1John4:10\">1JN 4:9–4:10</a></p>\n<h3>The risen Christ gives grace to sinful people</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John2:1\">1JN 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:34\">ROM 8:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:17-Heb2:18\">HEB 2:17–2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15-Heb5:2\">HEB 4:15–5:2</a></p>",
